-- 03-progressive-crystallization.cell
-- Tests: substrate transfer вҠў вҶ’ вҠў=, self-crystallization, oracle-gated evolution
--
-- A Cell program that takes a soft task, solves it via LLM (вҠў),
-- extracts the algorithm pattern, converts to a вҠў= expression,
-- then verifies the crystal against test cases. If all pass,
-- the soft cell is replaced by its crystallized form.
-- The cell literally evolves from вҠў (soft/LLM) to вҠў= (hard/deterministic).
-- This is substrate transfer as a runtime operation.

вҠў task
  given description вүЎ "Given a list of numbers, return the top 3 largest."
  given test-inputs[] вүЎ [
    [7, 2, 9, 4, 1, 8, 3],
    [1, 1, 1, 1, 1],
    [100, 200],
    [5, 3, 8, 1, 9, 2, 7, 4, 6]
  ]
  given test-expected[] вүЎ [
    [9, 8, 7],
    [1, 1, 1],
    [200, 100],
    [9, 8, 7]
  ]
  yield description, test-inputs, test-expected

  вҠЁ test-inputs has same length as test-expected
  вҠЁ each test-expected entry is sorted descending

вҠў solve-soft
  given taskвҶ’description
  given taskвҶ’test-inputs
  yield solution, outputs[]

  вҲҙ Solve В«taskвҶ’descriptionВ». For each input in В«taskвҶ’test-inputsВ»,
    work through the problem step by step using natural language
    reasoning. Produce the answer for each input.

  вҠЁ outputs has same length as test-inputs
  вҠЁ each output is a list of numbers sorted descending
  вҠЁ each output has at most 3 elements

вҠў extract-pattern
  given solve-softвҶ’solution
  given solve-softвҶ’outputs
  yield algorithm

  вҲҙ Read В«solve-softвҶ’solutionВ». What deterministic algorithm did you use?
    Express it as a numbered sequence of mechanical steps.
    No subjective judgment, no "think about it" вҖ” only operations
    a machine could execute without an LLM.

  вҠЁ algorithm is a numbered list of steps
  вҠЁ algorithm contains only deterministic operations (sort, take, compare)
  вҠЁ algorithm does not reference any specific input values

вҠў crystallize
  given extract-patternвҶ’algorithm
  yield hard-body

  вҲҙ Convert В«extract-patternвҶ’algorithmВ» into a single вҠў= expression.
    The expression must be deterministic code that replaces the вҲҙ body
    of solve-soft. Use only: sort, take, len, min.

  вҠЁ hard-body is a valid вҠў= expression
  вҠЁ hard-body contains no natural language
  вҠЁ hard-body takes an input list and returns a list

вҠў verify-crystal
  given crystallizeвҶ’hard-body
  given taskвҶ’test-inputs
  given taskвҶ’test-expected
  yield pass-all, results[], failures[]

  вҲҙ Apply В«crystallizeвҶ’hard-bodyВ» to each input in В«taskвҶ’test-inputsВ».
    Compare each result with В«taskвҶ’test-expectedВ».
    Record pass/fail for each case.

  вҠЁ results has same length as test-inputs
  вҠЁ failures is empty if and only if pass-all = true
  вҠЁ if pass-all then every result matches expected

вҠў emit-crystallized
  given verify-crystalвҶ’pass-all
  given verify-crystalвҶ’failures
  given crystallizeвҶ’hard-body
  given В§solve-soft
  yield crystallized-cell, substrate-transfer

  вҲҙ If В«verify-crystalвҶ’pass-allВ» is true:
    Produce the crystallized version of В«В§solve-softВ» by replacing
    the вҲҙ body with В«crystallizeвҶ’hard-bodyВ» and adding в–ё crystallized.
    This IS substrate transfer: вҠў вҶ’ вҠў=.
    If pass-all is false: substrate-transfer = false, explain why.

  вҠЁ if pass-all then crystallized-cell contains "вҠў="
  вҠЁ if pass-all then crystallized-cell contains "в–ё crystallized"
  вҠЁ if pass-all then substrate-transfer = true

  вҠЁ? on failure:
    retry with В«verify-crystalвҶ’failuresВ» appended to prompt
    max 2 attempts
